  "texts": [
    "The subjects are required to perform 5 classes of activities: random, saccades, read text, smooth pursuit and blinks.",
    "The total data volume is 9.2 GB.",
    "The ground truth is labeled at 100Hz and consists of two parts for each label: (1) a binary value indicating whether there was an eye blink or not; (2) human-labeled pupil center coordinates.",
    "Task description• Input: Raw event stream (x i, y i, t i, p i) of recorded eye movement.",
    "• Task: Predict the pupil center spatial coordinate (x, y) at required timestamps (same frequency as the ground truth) in the input space."
  ],
